Q: Scenario: Multiple ASGs with different scaling metrics. How? A: Configure target tracking or step policies per ASG.
458.
Q: EC2 cost optimization tips? A: Reserved/spot instances, rightsizing, delete unused volumes, schedule stop/start for dev instances.
459.
Q: Scenario: EC2 needs multi-region backup for compliance. How? A: Cross-region AMI copy, EBS snapshot replication.
460.
Q: EC2 patching best practices? A: Test in dev, automate via Systems Manager Patch Manager, schedule maintenance window.
461.
Q: EC2 security best practices? A: IAM roles, least privilege, encryption, VPC isolation, security group restrictions.
462.
Q: Scenario: Application cannot reach DB in different AZ. Solution? A: Check route tables, security group, VPC peering.
463.
Q: EC2 Spot + Reserved hybrid. Scenario? A: Reserved for base load, Spot for burst workloads.
464.
Q: Scenario: EC2 disk performance bottleneck. Fix? A: Use provisioned IOPS, higher instance type, EBS-optimized instances.
465.
Q: EC2 with high network throughput requirement. Solution? A: Enhanced networking enabled (ENA), placement group, higher network instance type.
466.
Q: Scenario: EC2 instance compromised. Steps? A: Isolate, snapshot, investigate, rotate keys, redeploy.
467.
Q: What is EC2 instance recovery? A: Automatically recovers instance on underlying hardware failure without changing instance ID.
468.
Q: Scenario: Recovery fails. Next step? A: Stop/start instance, contact AWS Support if hardware issue persists.
469.
Q: EC2 monitoring for cost anomaly. How? A: CloudWatch + Budgets alerts + Cost Explorer.
470.
Q: Scenario: Auto Scaling not triggering. Check? A: CloudWatch metric, policy configuration, cooldown period.
471.
Q: EC2 lifecycle hooks? A: Pause ASG scale-in/out to perform custom actions (drain connections, backup).
472.
Q: Scenario: Need zero-downtime deployment. Solution? A: Blue/Green deployment with ELB and ASG.
473.
Q: EC2 multi-tenancy compliance issues? A: Use dedicated hosts if regulatory requirements demand physical isolation.
474.
Q: Scenario: EC2 instances need auditing for security changes. How? A: CloudTrail logs, Config rules, CloudWatch Events.
475.
Q: EC2 high availability checklist? A: Multi-AZ, ELB, ASG, health checks, snapshots, monitoring.
476.
Q: Scenario: Application requires sub-second failover. Solution? A: Cluster placement group, pre-warmed standby instances.
477.
Q: EC2 integration with S3 & EFS for shared storage. Scenario? A: Mount EFS across EC2; use S3 SDK for object storage.
478.
Q: Scenario: EBS snapshot restore slow. How? A: Use fast snapshot restore option.
479.
Q: How to secure instance metadata? A: IMDSv2 enforced, limit role privileges.
480.
Q: Scenario: EC2 cross-region DR test. Approach? A: Replicate AMI/snapshots, deploy test instances, failover validation.
481.
Q: How to prevent accidental termination? A: Enable termination protection.
482.
Q: Scenario: Instance terminated despite protection. Cause? A: Force terminate via API, instance was not protected at launch.
483.
Q: EC2 network troubleshooting steps? A: Check ENI, SG, NACL, route tables, VPC endpoints, DNS resolution.
484.
Q: Scenario: EC2 cannot resolve private domain. Fix? A: Check Route53 private hosted zone, VPC association, DHCP option sets.
485.
Q: EC2 monitoring for SLA compliance. Approach? A: CloudWatch SLI metrics, alarm on deviation, Auto Recovery.
486.
Q: Scenario: EC2 load balancer unhealthy threshold too sensitive. Solution? A: Adjust health check thresholds or intervals.
487.
Q: EC2 instance cannot mount EFS NFS. Fix? A: Security group, mount target, subnet route, NFS client configuration.
488.
Q: Scenario: High cost due to idle EC2. Solution? A: Stop unused instances, use spot for dev/test, schedule start/stop.
489.
Q: EC2 audit trail for compliance. Tools? A: CloudTrail, Config, Security Hub.
490.
Q: Scenario: EC2 RDS access denied after instance recreation. Solution? A: IAM role attachment, security group inbound, subnet route.
491.
Q: EC2 instance CPU credit exhaustion. Scenario? A: T2/T3 burstable instance; monitor with CloudWatch, consider larger or standard instance.
492.
Q: Scenario: Auto Scaling group not scaling to max. Fix? A: Check ASG MaxSize, CloudWatch metrics, scaling policies.
493.
Q: EC2 spot interruption notice. Response? A: Use two-minute notice for checkpointing or migrate workload.
494.
Q: EC2 instance stuck pending. Scenario? A: Insufficient capacity in AZ; try different AZ or instance type.
495.
Q: Scenario: EC2 fails after AMI update. Solution? A: Validate AMI, dependencies, test in staging, rollback if needed.
496.
Q: EC2 instance fails system status check repeatedly. Approach? A: Stop/start, check EBS, contact AWS for hardware replacement.
497.
Q: Scenario: EC2 memory leak in app. Detection? A: CloudWatch custom metrics, detailed monitoring, logs.
498.
Q: EC2 instance metadata poisoning attack. Prevention? A: IMDSv2 enforced, restrict IAM privileges, patch OS.
499.
Q: Scenario: EC2 fleet experiencing intermittent network failures across AZs. How to troubleshoot and mitigate? A: Check VPC/subnet routing, SG/NACL rules, placement groups, instance type network limits, monitor CloudWatch metrics, enable enhanced networking, and consider cross-AZ traffic optimization.
500.
Q: Scenario: Multi-AZ EC2 deployment costs exceeding budget while maintaining HA. Optimization strategy? A: Keep minimal standby in secondary AZ, use Spot instances for non-critical workloads, rightsizing, enable auto-start/stop for dev/test, monitor costs via AWS Budgets, enforce lifecycle policies for snapshots and AMIs.
